General infos/tips about Linux Commands:
------------------------------------------------------------------------

you write in the front of the command "sudo" if you need only for a one command more permissions.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

to be root: sudo -i, to exit the root: exit

------------------------------------------------------------------------

to open .tar.gz files: tar -zxvf name.tar.gz

------------------------------------------------------------------------

to depackage a .deb file: sudo dpkg -i name.deb

------------------------------------------------------------------------

write in a protected file: sudo gedit "path"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

when you write mkdir -p "path" the not existing part of the path will be created too!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

to update something is like change files/folders/index/etc. 
to upgrade something is to install newer versions of something

------------------------------------------------------------------------

if you want to install something you have to "sudo apt install...."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

if you are at "HOME" and you click Strg+H then there will be more folders and these are the folders for your settings (for the programs you have installed)
